-- Three-Month Copper Futures Decline 0.8% to $6,600 a Ton on LME; Tin Climbs
-- Glenys Sim
-- 2010-06-17T00:05:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/three-month-copper-futures-decline-0-8-to-6-600-a-ton-on-lme-tin-climbs.html

          
          
             Three-month copper futures declined
0.8 percent to $6,600 a metric ton on the London Metal Exchange,
dropping for a second day. Aluminum and zinc also fell, while
tin gained.  
